is a managed DNS(Domain Name System).
DNS- Collection of rules and records 

The most common records:
  A: hostname to IPv4
  AAAA: hostname to IPv6
  CNAME: hostname to hostname
  Alias: hostname to AWS resource.
  
  
Web Browser makes a DNS request to route53 through hostname(myapp.mydomain.com) and gets back an IP; hence A record
Web Browser makes a HTTP request to an application server with an http IP and gets back an http response.

Route53 can use: public domain names(.com) or private domain names(.internal).
has advanced features: Load Balancing, health checks, routing policies.

